snippet.title: Behind the News
snippet.description:
For the past 50 years, BTN has been a world leader in children's news & kids news. As part of the Australian Broadcasting Corporation, BTN has introduced the news & current events to upper-primary students in Australia and around the world - but it isn't just for kids. BTN assists people of all ages by breaking down current issues and events in a high-energy, fun way - all while providing background information that isn’t usually given by other news bulletins.
 
We have 1000s of stories on all sorts of topics - if you're looking for help to understand something, you'll probably find it on BTN. http://www.abc.net.au/btn/ 

Follow us on Social Media:

snippet.title: Jordan Ware
snippet.description: Jordan Waré is grammy- award winning producer, violinist, and one half of the indie group, October's Child. The trained violinist has performed worldwide with such acts as Madonna, Quincy Jones, Justin TImberlake and Wyclef Jean. A native New Yorker who moved to Los Angeles in mid-2014, Waré has continued to further develop his production sound, producing for numerous up and coming artists including, Avonlea, Elley Duhé & Brent Faiyaz . Waré touts his greatest accolade as co-producing the ballad that would become the hit record, "Where Are Ü Now," featuring Justin Bieber on Diplo and Skrillex's Jack Ü album, which won a Grammy's in 2016 for Best Dance Recording and Best Dance/Electronic Album.

snippet.description:
¡Bienvenido al canal oficial de Euronews en YouTube!  

A todas horas, nuestro equipo de 500 periodistas de más de 30 nacionalidades diferentes reúne noticias con una perspectiva imparcial, más allá de los contenidos de los titulares y las voces de toda Europa y el mundo. Nuestro canal de YouTube tiene todo esto y más, ofreciendo contenidos seleccionados y originales de la principal fuente de noticias internacionales de Europa.

Nuestra misión es capacitar a la gente para que se forme su propia opinión. Confiamos en la inteligencia y la capacidad de las personas para decidir por sí mismas y tratamos de ofrecer a nuestra audiencia la mayor diversidad de puntos de vista a través de un periodismo inexcusablemente imparcial.

Euronews nació de la voluntad de crear un fuerte canal de noticias europeo independiente. Como único medio de comunicación internacional con una perspectiva europea, Euronews es el lugar al que el mundo acude para escuchar lo que Europa tiene que decir.

snippet.title: Maktoob
snippet.description:
Maktoob is a media initiative based Delhi, in India. It was founded in the southern state Kerala, in March, 2014, with an aim of ensuring an equal and unbiased space for discussion, dialogue and dissemination of information and news. Maktoob publishes news and features in English.

In the recent decades, media ownership had concentrated in the hands of few corporations and conglomerates. This has lead to a narrowing of range of voices and opinions being expressed. And here, Maktoob is trying to make a change. Through news, views and analyses of  ground reports, Maktoob aims to play the part of a small media that aids in a big revolution of justice, liberty and equality.

Maktoob showcases continuous efforts to empower individual citizen and promote democratic ideals through the spread of accurate and humanized editorial content.  The Caste, Class conflicts of diverse Indian society is given utmost editorial importance and we stand against the fascist ideologies.

snippet.title: indusdotnews
snippet.description:
Aap Media Network believes in an informed and engaged citizenry, essential for a constitutional democracy. We provide relevant, important, timely and accurate news to the audience and opportunities for public discourse and interaction. In doing so, we are accountable to our viewers. We cherish our independence and strive to be objective and fair.

Our news-gathering and analyses seek to meet high editorial standards. We aim to inculcate civility in the discourse, an unfortunate casualty of the race for television rating points.

Our English-language channel, Indus News, aims to present Pakistan’s perspective on issues of regional and global importance through an inside-out view. We believe the viewer receives the greatest benefit from news and analyses in a global-to-local context. In this, we seek to bring to international audiences the complexity often missed in the coverage of this region

snippet.title: T-BOON Productions
snippet.description: T-Boon Productions is the result of creative writing , producing and directing by Thijs Boonen aka Boon. He grew up in a small village near the border with the Netherlands in Belgium. His mother (Hilde Keunen) is a professional painter and sculptor who introduced Boon to the fine arts from a very young age. After graduating the Brussels film academy R.I.T.S. in 2004 he worked professionally in the movie and TV scene in Belgium and Europe. It was love that brought him to Tucson ,AZ. This change of scenery inspired him to make his first short feature Mariachi. This channel will show you previews of his work. Hope you enjoy, Boon

snippet.title: Gabriel Jose Rodriguez
snippet.description:
Musician, producer, DJ, and Funk music enthusiast alike, Gabriel hails out of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Gabriel drew much of his musical influence from his father, a well-known Latin composer and lead musician for his band La Unica.

Interested in music all his life, Gabriel pursued it further at Eastern University where he completed a degree in Music Composition and Electronic Music.

When he’s not performing, he spends time in his studio creating his own music and completing client projects. Although he is well versed in all genres of music, some of Gabriel’s favorite genres to mix include Funk/Motown, Oldies, Hip Hop, R&B, Top 40, and Pop music.

Aided by a decade of piano lessons and a musically influenced upbringing, Gabriel’s diverse background lends to his effortless ability to blend a variety of genres; creating the perfect backdrop for any event!

snippet.title: The StudyTube Project
snippet.description:
Hello! 

The outbreak of the Coronavirus pandemic is having unprecedented impacts across the world: schools and universities are closing, GCSE and A-Level exams are cancelled - but that doesn’t mean education needs to stop.

So, we’ve decided to do something about it: welcome to The StudyTube Project!

We’ve all teamed up to try and bring calm in these times of high anxiety and stress. Each day for the foreseeable future, we’ll be taking it in turns to teach you something, or share an area of education we’re passionate about or specialize in. This is a channel to keep you busy, keep you learning or even just to give you somewhere to escape to! Any profits made from Adsense will go straight to charities helping fight COVID-19.

Let's come together as a community and support one another through this confusing time.

There will be a brand new video every day at 6pm, as well as regular content on our Instagram: @thestudytubeproject !

snippet.title: Yves Dhar - Cello Makes Everything Better
snippet.description: Chh-helloooo everyone, and welcome to my Youtube channel!  As a concert cellist, teacher, and innovator, I invite you to join in watching some mostly fun, sometimes probing, and hopefully illuminating videos that revolve around the best instrument in the world.  There should be a little something for everyone -- fun videos for those who are curious about the cello, behind-the-scenes interviews and footage for the serious fans, and advanced instructional "tips" for the obsessed.  Whether you watch just one video or become a loyal subscriber, I hope to show you that the magic of music is all around us, even when we least expect it, and that "Life without cello is cruel!"  Thanks for watching!

snippet.title: Anya Dillard
snippet.description:
Lifestyle ✩ Activism ✩ Entrepreneurship

Hello all! My name's Anya. I'm an 18-year-old activist, philanthropist, social entrepreneur, and content creator with big dreams of changing the world through self-expression, mobilization, and advocacy. Though I've been a sociopolitical changemaker since I was 12, I've been a woman of service since I was 5 years old and have dedicated my platforms to advocating for human rights, mentoring young leaders, and spreading social/ political awareness about important issues to my followers. I wanted to create this channel to not just share my experiences as a radical Gen-Zer, but to share my experiences as an afro-Caribbean girl, workaholic, college student, aspiring filmmaker, and a restless creative as well. So welcome to my mind, my life, my world! Hope you don't get lost ♡

IG/ Tik Tok/Twitter/ Facebook = @iamajdillard

snippet.title: Comrade Rhys
snippet.description:
Hello comrades, it's Comrade Rhys. I'm a Welsh Marxist-Leninist who uploads political videos to promote and defend Socialism, as it's my job to inform you, whether you like it or not. I upload a video on this whenever I have the time, as my work schedule and personal life often eats into the time that I have to make videos. The party that I support is the CPB (Communist Party of Britain). I came round to supporting them after undergoing some serious self-criticism over my support for the CPGB-ML who over the years have shown their very reactionary positions. 

I am constantly asked the question of what got me so into Socialism. I cannot answer it with anything better than experiencing life under Capitalism; wage labour, purchasing goods, times of economic crisis etc. I then wanted to start reflecting on that experience through looking at Marxist literature, which is what gave me the informed decision to become a Marxist-Leninist. 

Keep the red flag flying, comrades!

snippet.title: ChickenWire
snippet.description:
Interested in politics or going to Malaysia? Want to debate? It’s time to give YOU a voice. 
Every other day at 4pm. 

Each video is a forum for debate rather than a lecture. By opening up the conversation its providing a benefit to the country and the world as a whole and has the potential to make real change. 

ChickeWire stared off as a comedy channel and I still like to poke fun from time to time. The name ChickenWire actually comes from a song I made that went viral when I was younger https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qZ7HwBQ3C6o&t=7s

Ever since I've been making the odd political video when the UK election 2017 came round was when I gained a lot of views for this documentary I made https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ol9zSvJxj3M&t=10s

It was then I realised that even though I don't always predict things correctly I have a skill for seeing an oversight into how the UK works and I'm passionate about providing that information.

Explore the world. Subscribe.

snippet.title: Nathan Zed
snippet.description:
I'm Nathan Zed

"DON'T FORGET TO SUBSCRIBE!!" I type, as I sit at my laptop, the rest of my body completely motionless.The click-clack sound of the keyboard echoing in my ears long after I had finished typing. I remain still for what seems like an eternity, only moving to wipe the single tear streaming from my right eye. "Not like this...", I let the whisper escape my lips loud enough for anyone nearby to hear me.
No one is nearby.

snippet.title: Beneath The Glitterball
snippet.description:
Welcome to a unique and sociologically space where we dive deep into sociological theories,
audio analysis, film theory, and all things Madonna. This channel is dedicated to exploring the
intersections of culture and society through engaging content and insightful commentary.

What We Offer:

• In-depth Analyses: Thought-provoking discussions on sociological theories and their application
in contemporary media, cultural sociology, and critical theory.

• Multimedia Content: A variety of videos covering audio analysis, sound studies, film reviews,
cinema studies, and cultural critiques.

• M Focus: Special segments and series dedicated to the life, career, history, and influence
of Madonna.

• Personalized Learning: Request individual teaching sessions and additional materials tailored to
your interests, including sociology lessons and theoretical insights.

cinema studies, and cultural critiques.

of Madonna.

your interests, including sociology lessons and theoretical insights.

snippet.title: Samuel Lee Blue
snippet.description: Samuel Lee Blue (born February 17, 1996) is a           St. Louis-born singer, rapper, songwriter, record engineer, and producer. Music was his refuge from the hardships of his youth, and now, residing in the Florida panhandle with his family, he serves as a church pianist, demonstrating his continued commitment to music and community. A devoted husband to Katie Blue, and father to Samuel Lee Blue II, Samuel's passion extends to inspiring the next generation through his music. His songs reflect his journey, struggles, and hope for a brighter future, all while glorifying God.

snippet.title: Merlin Fulcher
snippet.description: Merlin Fulcher is an architectural journalist, writer and broadcaster based in London and reporting on key issues affecting economies, society and the built environment in the UK and beyond. Fulcher has more than a decade's experience in architectural reporting and is currently competitions editor, focussing on procurement, for both Architects' Journal and Architectural Review. Since 2017 he has also been director of tours at London's Architecture Foundation based at the Royal College of Art, leading a team of expert guides in the creation of a highly popular programme exploring complex geographic and design themes across the city.  His other writing -- including reviews, analysis and poems -- has been published by Construction News, New Civil Engineer, the Evening Standard, Different Skies, Counterfire and Tribune. Fulcher holds an MA in Modern History from Lady Margaret Hall, University of Oxford. Since 2020, Fulcher has been Vlogging under the banner Untitled UK on YouTube.

snippet.title: Robotaki
snippet.description:
There is a lot more behind the name and the mask than most people may perceive. Coming in to the spotlight with his top-tier remix work (Just the Remixes.), and being recognized for his impeccable sounds, Preston Chin, the man behind the moniker has prepared himself to take on a much greater task. 

A task that entails enveloping the world with a powerful new take on funk, Electronic and disco. A responsibility to brighten peoples days and to make people dance. A quest to bring a fresh musical experience to humans that has never been done before. 

Armed with a Master's degree in Cell Biology, a carefully curated sound and support from the likes of Porter Robinson and Madeon,  he's the man to accomplish this mission.

snippet.title: NOS
snippet.description:
De NOS is de grootste nieuwsorganisatie van Nederland. Grote nieuwsgebeurtenissen kan je hier LIVE volgen. En elke vrijdagmiddag een nieuw RONDJE BINNENHOF, onze politieke YouTube-serie rondom de formatie. Mis niets en abonneer je op ons YouTube-kanaal.

Reageer ook vooral onder onze video's, we zijn benieuwd naar jouw mening. Dit YouTube-kanaal is een plek waar iedereen zich kan uitspreken, met respect voor elkaar. We willen geen scheldwoorden, beledigingen, bedreigingen, discriminatie, off-topic-berichten, spam en reclame-uitingen. We laten liefst alle reacties staan maar grijpen in als dat nodig en mogelijk is. Zie je iets wat we beter kunnen doen? Stuur dan een berichtje naar social@nos.nl

Je vindt de NOS de hele dag door op radio en televisie met het NOS Journaal, op NOS.nl en Facebook en Twitter. Altijd. Overal. NOS.

snippet.title: Domonique Cynthia
snippet.description:
The power of the creative mind! There’s nothing else like it. I love problem solving through innovation. I found a passion for using my creativity, videography and storytelling skills to help showcase diversity across universities globally. My ultimate goal is to encourage people of color to see ourselves thriving in institutions that we have traditionally been underrepresented in. I aim to ensure that the doors opened for me are left opened even wider for those who will come next.

I am fascinated by a camera’s ability to capture the deepest intricacies of the human mind. Filmmaking is empowering. It allows me to create visually-captivating and emotionally-stirring stories. What’s most fascinating is a camera’s ability to be the tool that helps me continuously learn. With my eye in the viewfinder, there’s no longer a barrier between my creativity and the infinite inspiration the world offers. This is my passion. 
 

Business Inquiries: partner.domoniquecynthia@gmail.com

snippet.title: Zee. Fashion
snippet.description: Peaky Blinders is a gangster family epic set in Birmingham, England, in 1919, several months after the end of the First World War in November 1918. The story centres on the Peaky Blinders gang and their ambitious and highly cunning boss Tommy Shelby (Cillian Murphy). The gang comes to the attention of Major Chester Campbell (Sam Neill), a Detective Chief Inspector in the Royal Irish Constabulary (R.I.C.) sent over by Winston Churchill from Belfast, where he had been sent to clean up the city of the Irish Republican Army (I.R.A.), Communists, gangs and common criminals.[4][5] Winston Churchill (played by Andy Nyman in Series 1 and Richard McCabe in Series 2) charged him with suppressing disorder and uprising in Birmingham and recovering a stolen cache of arms meant to be shipped to Libya.[6][7] The first series concludes on 3 December 1919 – "Black Star Day", the event where the Peaky Blinders plan to take over Billy Kimber's betting pitches at the Worcester Races.

snippet.title: VOA Thai
snippet.description:
วีโอเอเป็นองค์กรข่าวระหว่างประเทศที่ใหญ่ที่สุดของสหรัฐฯ เผยแพร่ข่าวสารบนสื่อหลายช่องทางเป็นภาษาอังกฤษและภาษาต่างประเทศกว่า 45 ภาษา ผู้รับข่าวสารของเราอยู่ในประเทศที่เข้าถึงสื่อเสรีได้อย่างจำกัดหรือไม่สามารถเข้าถึงสื่อเสรีได้เลย
วีโอเอก่อตั้งขึ้นในปี พ.ศ. 2485 มุ่งมั่นเสนอข่าวที่เป็นความจริง ครอบคลุม และเป็นอิสระ งบประมาณทั้งหมดของวีโอเอมาจากผู้เสียภาษีชาวอเมริกัน เราเป็นส่วนหนึ่งของหน่วยงาน U.S. Agency for Global Media

พันธกิจของวีโอเอและความเป็นอิสระในการทำข่าว กฎบัตรของวีโอเอ รับรองเป็นกฎหมายระบุว่า
1. วีโอเอจะต้องทำงานในฐานะแหล่งข่าวที่น่าเชื่อถือและเป็นที่พึ่งได้อย่างสม่ำเสมอ มีความถูกต้อง เป็นกลางและครบถ้วน
2. วีโอเอจะทำงานเพื่อสะท้อนภาพของประเทศอเมริกา โดยไม่เลือกเสนอเฉพาะส่วนใดส่วนหนึ่งของสังคมสหรัฐฯเท่านั้น ดังนั้นวีโอเอจะเสนอข้อมูลที่สมดุลและมีความครอบคลุมสำหรับความคิดแบบอเมริกันและสถาบันต่างๆของประเทศ
3. วีโอเอจะเสนอรายงานเกี่ยวกับนโยบายของสหรัฐฯอย่างกระจ่างชัดและมีประสิทธิภาพ และจะเสนอประเด็นที่ถูกหยิบยกมาพูดถึงและแสดงความคิดเห็นเกี่ยวกับนโยบายเหล่านั้นอย่างมีความรับผิดชอบ
